  <name>Vinyl</name>
  <summary>Elegant music player</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      Vinyl is a simple and elegant adwaita music player, which aims to provide a simple codebase for developers,
      while simple users get the same or more features as in other music players. Flawless integrated with the GNOME desktop, 
      Vinyl provides a simple user-friendly interface, MPRIS support, lyrics support and more. Vinyl is the first player with 
      a good lyrics (.lrc) support.
    </p>

    <p>Features include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Very simple user-friendly interface inspired by amberol.</li>
      <li>Play of music using GStreamer.</li>
      <li>Viewing of lyrics like listview.</li>
      <li>MPRIS support for controlling Vinyl from other applications.</li>
      <li>A fully responsive interface using GTK and Libadwaita.</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

